#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:1
msgid "ABI Mangling extension for C/C++ ABI in VTK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:3
msgid ""
"Using the C++ feature `inline namespace` VTK is able to apply ABI mangling "
"to VTK without affecting the API interface in code. This feature allows for "
"separately compiled VTK libraries isolated in their own translation units to "
"be linked in the same application without symbol conflicts at runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:8
msgid ""
"This feature was \"experimental\" due to lack of  CI testing and missing "
"manglings for C ABIs in VTK. Both of these missing components are now added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:12
msgid ""
"A change from the experimental version to the current version is the "
"splitting of concerns for the ABI namespace. Previously, "
"`VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_NAME` allowed the injection of additional attributes into "
"the namespace such as `__attribute__ ((visibility (\\\"hidden\\\")))`. The "
"`VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_NAME` is now guarded to follow a subset of the C++ "
"namespace naming rules (it must match the regular expression `^[a-zA-Z0-9_]+"
"$`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:19
msgid "Must contain only lower-case or upper-letters, numbers, or underscores"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:20
msgid "Must contain one(1) or more characters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:21
msgid ""
"Cannot use nested or anonymous namespace names (ie. no `::` or empty names)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:23
msgid ""
"Attribute inject is now supported as a separate feature flag "
"`VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_ATTRIBUTES` which takes a string of attributes to inject."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:26
msgid ""
"Example defining a ABI namespace `vtk9_custom` which applies the "
"`visibility(\"hidden\")` attribute to all of the VTK bits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:29
msgid ""
"cmake -DVTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_NAME=vtk9_custom \\\n"
"      -DVTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_ATTRIBUTES=\"__attribute__ ((visibility (\\"
"\"hidden\\\")))\" \\\n"
"      $source_path\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:35
msgid ""
"The C ABIs previously skipped by the ABI mangling feature are now included. "
"Most of the C ABIs have added macros for compatibility in VTK module code. "
"While the macros allow for use of the unmangled name in code, they do not "
"allow for loading functions via the DLL interface by the unmangled names. "
"While the `inline namespace` wrapped mangling allows the injection of extra "
"attributes, the C ABI mangling currently does not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:42
msgid ""
"Configure warnings were added when configuring features without ABI mangling "
"support when the `VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_NAME` is set. While it is still possible "
"to build VTK with these configurations, it is not recommended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:46
msgid "Notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:47
msgid ""
"This change does not affect VTK builds that are not using the "
"`VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE` feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:48
msgid "Third party libraries still do not support ABI mangling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/abi-mangling-extension.md:49
msgid "VTK Wrappings still do not support ABI mangling (ie. Python/Java/etc.)."
msgstr ""
